
This monitor is meant to help solve blocking problems in SQL Servers.
For background see

* http://support.microsoft.com/kb/224453
* http://www.informit.com/articles/article.aspx?p=26949

You will need to install in SQL Server the stored procedure you will
find in this article: http://support.microsoft.com/kb/271509/

The Ruby script in this directory calls the stored procedure at 30
seconds intervals and saves the output in separate files.
